{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ee49985c-0b88-43a3-8710-667d4dd90f5a","content":"Here's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform on .NET 8:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- \\\n  --treenode-filter \"/TestCategory=Integration\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Option mapping:**\n\n| VSTest (old) | Microsoft.Testing.Platform (new) |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` | `--treenode-filter \"/TestCategory=Integration\"` |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Key things to note:**\n\n1. Everything after `--` is forwarded to the test platform runner.\n2. You need the corresponding NuGet packages in your test project:\n   - `Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild`\n   - `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`\n   - `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`\n   - `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`\n   - `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`\n3. The filter syntax changes — `--treenode-filter` uses a path-like syntax (`/Property=Value`). If you prefer the old expression syntax, you can keep `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` before the `--` separator, though behavior may differ slightly.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ffe305b9-42c6-46c7-9f9e-38062ffcacab","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing tooling, not a codebase task. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences with Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n- `--filter` becomes `--filter` (same, but can also use `--treenode-filter`)\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` (with Microsoft.CodeCoverage)\n\n\n- `--blame-crash` maps to `--crashdump`\n- `--blame-hang` and `--blame-hang-timeout` become `--hangdump` and `--hangdump-timeout` respectively\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform in .NET 8+, you can still use `dotnet test` and pass platform-specific options after `--`, though the exact syntax depends on whether you're using the new test platform directly or through the compatibility layer. With `dotnet test`, the Microsoft.Testing.Platform integration uses the `--` separator to pass platform-specific arguments like `--report-trx`, `--coverage`, and diagnostic options. Alternatively, I can run the test executable directly with `dotnet run --project` and pass those same arguments, which gives more direct control over the test runner behavior on .NET 8. Completing the command with the remaining flags, then showing an alternative approach using `--filter` instead of `--treenode-filter` if they prefer to stick with the original VSTest syntax.","outputTokens":1434,"requestId":"E840:32B862:26BD07A:2936976:6A049406"},"id":"e7d6971b-100a-4090-8435-947a3dde58cb","timestamp":"2026-05-13T15:09:19.435Z","parentId":"db3524df-e120-45ae-8b10-c0399e87bec5"}
